modules.description: This module implements profiling functionality with support for tracking execution time and call counts of named code sections. It provides functions to wrap and measure arbitrary computations, selectively enable or disable profiling scopes, and generate diagnostic reports. Concrete use cases include performance analysis of critical code paths, identifying bottlenecks in algorithms, and logging execution metrics during test runs.

This module handles AST transformations for profiling, including counting function parameters, generating parameter expressions, and constructing module names from filenames. It operates on OCaml AST structures like expressions, structure items, and location data. It is used to inject profiling code into functions and modules based on their source structure.
